{
  "stem": "13313.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was number 1, and then in Dutch one would say [DUTCH], which means, street of justice.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because at the end of our streets was the Palace of Justice, the courts and everything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was a corner-- corner of the-- of the Road [? to Malin, ?] Brussels, and [DUTCH] right in the heart of Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No-- no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that point-- at that point, I recall, your-- the-- all the Jewish businesses were closed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You were not allowed to-- the moment they started deportation of the men, first-- men always first-- the-- all the Jewish businesses were-- were closed, and-- and confiscated, in a way.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Fortunately we had done quite well, and we had saved some money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- so we were living there not knowing what was going to happen, naturally devastated by the fact that our father and my mother's husband were gone-- was gone.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we didn't know what tomorrow was going to bring.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a total--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it so happened that the-- the Jewish community, through its central organizational body, was able to establish some contact with the people in the labor camps.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These were labor camps.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Matter of fact, I do recall, some how, that the name of the camp where my father was situated was a camp called Dannes Camir.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No, whether that's spelled D-A-N-N-E-S, I think so, Camir, C-A-M-I-R, which was one of the camps that helped build the fortifications for the Germans on the French coast, in the Atlantic French coast.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these were labor camps, not-- not extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
